Traffic Predictor Chatbot
This project is a chatbot-based traffic prediction system that helps users forecast traffic levels for a given date and hour. It uses historical data and a machine learning model (Linear Regression) to predict traffic intensity as Light, Moderate, or Heavy.

 Project Structure

Aicte_Project/
├── app/
│   ├── api.py              # Handles chatbot API routes
│   ├── traffic_logic.py    # Core traffic prediction logic
│   └── __init__.py         # Makes app a Python package
├── data/
│   └── traffic_data.csv    # Historical traffic data
├── notebooks/
│   └── analysis.ipynb      # EDA and model testing
├── run.py                  # Launches Flask server
├── requirements.txt        # Python libraries required
├── chat.html               # Chatbot UI
└── README.md               # Project documentation


 How to Run the Application

1. Create & Activate Virtual Environment
python3 -m venv ven                 # Create virtual environment
source ven/bin/activate            # Linux/macOS
ven\Scripts\activate               # Windows

2. Navigate to Project Folder
cd Aicte_Project

3. Install Required Libraries
pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Run the Flask Application
python3 run.py

5. Use the Chatbot
Open http://127.0.0.1:5000 in your browser to interact with the chatbot via chat.html.
